content:
Set Up Post-Chat Surveys for Messaging for In-App and Web

At the end of a Messaging for In-App and Web session, automatically send the customer a link to a Salesforce Feedback Management survey.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create messaging components:
Customize Application AND View Setup and Configuration
OR
System Administrator

To set up and edit Messaging channels:
Configure Messaging
To view channels:
View Setup and Configuration

Step 1: Create Your Survey
Create a survey in Salesforce Feedback Management. Include merge fields to personalize the text shown in the survey.
Generate and copy your survey link.

Step 2: Create an Auto-Response Messaging Component
Create an auto-response messaging component that's linked to your survey.
Enter introductory text without your survey link.
Customize your auto-response, click Add Format, select Web Page, and configure its properties.
Add parameter entries for each parameter in your survey URL.
Save your changes.

Step 3: Update Your Channel Settings
Associate your messaging component with the Messaging for In-App and Web channel.
Update the End Conversation field to select your auto-response component.

Step 4: Test Your Post-Chat Survey
Start and end a sample Messaging for In-App and Web session, verify that the survey was sent.
title: Set Up Post-Chat Surveys in Service Cloud
